The Biden-Harris Administration is using federal resources to respond to the massacres at Tops Friendly Market in Buffalo, New York, and Robb Elementary School in Uvalde, Texas. They are providing mental health resources and other supports for victims, including students. The United States Department of Agriculture (USDA) has programs to secure access to nutritious food in Buffalo and Uvalde. They are also supporting veterans and working on defusing conflict and building community. The administration is providing affordable access to broadband and resources to prevent targeted violence through the Department of Homeland Security (DHS) and The National Counterterrorism Center.